entry.title: Calidris minuta
entry.content: This bird is in breeding colour... much brighter orange-rufous than the colours of the Red-necked Stint - I have left the Red-necked Stints in for comparisons. In the primary picture you can also see the white 'line' across the mantle (upper back) of which the two lines from the rear appear as a loose V and is one of the diagnostic features of a Little Stint.

entry.title: Haematopus finschi
entry.content: Flagged 1N; the SIPO is smaller than an Australia POC, has visibly shorter legs and longer, thinner bill. In flight, the underwing is almost entirely white.
